{
  "text": "In a previous comparative study, memory recalls at the end of 1-h infusions of 0.2 or 0.6 \u00b5g/kg dexmedetomidine were significantly worse than in a placebo control group, and BIS recovered to baseline 4 h after stopping dexmedetomidine [CITATION_1] . We also found that PACU stays were longer with higher sedation score in the dexmedetomidine group than in the midazolam group. It has been previously suggested that proper control of infusion rate might help reduce delayed recovery from sedation [CITATION_2] . Atropine use (n) 1 (2) 5 (9) 0.098 Table 5 . Postoperative profiles.",
